        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;12/05/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 19:18:24</font>
        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=39"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=39')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="http://ulaa.coolfreehost.com"><img src="icon_Homepage.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Visit Ulaa's Homepage" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('http://edit.yahoo.com/config/send_webmesg?.target=nz_necro&.src=pg')"><img src="icon_yahoo.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Send Ulaa a Yahoo! Message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=68372&TOPIC_ID=8444&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=hunting+guides+54&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Here is my advice for getting outta UberHell. I made 2 full bubbles in 9hrs doing this.</P><P>Its really basic. Park your ass in CS and stay there. This works so much better if you have good CoV faction so my advice is to gain that before trying this, get to at least non Kos if you arent already.</P><P>Facing out from the beach make a pet a little to the right of the middle camp and have him guard the spot. You wont use him much but he is very useful occasionally and he is vital to successfully pull the Chests.</P><P>The rest is very easy. Dark/Root/Dot the wyverns on the cliff tops. If you have good CoV faction you can pull from both side of the "hook" which gives you about 35 or so spawn spots (not including the tower.) Even when the Multi kiters are out in force you can 95% of the time find a target.</P><P>Pet is there for the one wyv that is going to resist everything.</P><P>The trick here is also to pull the chests. Noone ever seems to know about these guys and if the multi kiters are getting too bad you can simply go and sit and pull the chests by themselves underwater.</P><P>Basically, facing out from the beach to the right of the middle camp there is a little dip in the beach front. With DMF up and Jboots (VITAL NOTE : Dont do this without JBoots/SOW and full health or you are dead cause you will never make it back to the beach.) run straight into the water. You will see ahead of you a boat wreck on the bottom.</P><P>Run up to the bow of the wreck, just as you are going to run into it turn and run up to the surface and back to the beach. Hopefully you have aggroed the chest and its following you. You will take a couple of hits but dont worry too much about them. Even if it stuns you you will make it to the beach.</P><P>Pet will aggro, if you havent been hit, target chest and send pet in. From here its Dark/Fear easy. Drop a splurt and or a Bond on it and you will KS the pet. These bad boys hit like trains so dont let the pet tank em for too long. Be prepared to root em.</P><P>The Chests drop the rarer quest gems (I got Crushed Black Marbel, Crushed Coral off them etc) the Wyvs drop the more common quest gems and cash gems. Have a list of which is which when you go into the zone. I was keeping them all and then selling the cash gems in my home town cause you will get a 20% better price than from the otters.</P><P>NOTES:<BR>If you do this correctly you can easily and safely pull 4 Mobs every 6 or so Minutes, (Chests are a six min spawn, so the routine is usually Chest, Wyv, Wyv, Chest). I have never been in this zone when someone else was pulling chests. If you want just go sit underwater and park pet near bow of boat and pull chests constantly. This is actually a better kill ratio than the DE's in Neriak and noone ever does it.</P><P>Otters start off NON Kos to everybody and you can buy food but not drink from the two otter merchants.</P><P>Drakes have an AE DD/Debuff thats nasty if you are caught in it.</P><P>There is no faction hit for killing chests/wyvs/drakes. The only faction hit is for killing NAMED mobs. There are Two, Yvolcarn and Azureake. Neither drop anything good, Yvolcarn summons and is unsnareable so just dont go there.</P><P>Drakes will ignore you killing Wyvs.</P><P>Azuraeke the "named" drake will NOT ignore you killing Wyvs. He will attack and kill you if you have aggroed a Wyv. So if he is up, pull from the beach, just dark the Wyv to pull to beach and root once they get down.</P><P>Good luck, I did this from about 52-55. The Wyvs will still be blue through to 55 tho some of them will be light blue. If you die there is often no rez available as there arent many clerics in this zone.</P><P>Bow Down for a Defiler walks amongst you!<BR>55 DE Necromancer<BR>Karana server<BR>Proud Member of The Silent Watch<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

